HEADWORD: Jequirity bean
<hw>Je*quir"i*ty bean`</hw> }</mhw>. <ety>[Prob. fr. a native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The seed of the wild licorice
(<spn>Abrus precatorius</spn>) used by the people of India for beads in
rosaries and necklaces, as a standard weight, etc.; -- called also
<altname>jumble bead</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

